metadata.name: zancannabis #375
metadata.description:
zancannabis is a celebration of 4/20 2023 and is of course a respectful parody of the artwork from the legend that is zancan.
this artwork uses code to randomly place illustrations of cannabis plants created using midjourney ai with post-production in Illustrator and Photoshop.

The work is in no way related to the artist zancan and is not intended to fool anyone into thinking so thus does not affect the original artists market or value.

metadata.name: Aura #87
metadata.description:
Each artwork in this collection combines handpicked color palettes and simple shapes to create visually appealing pieces.

Aura showcases a captivating mix of colors and minimalist tilted rectangles, forming a harmonious and balanced composition. 

Collecting this piece means owning a cool work of generative art and supporting the artist's passion and creativity.

metadata.name: Supernal Memories #291
metadata.description:
With its layered bursts of color, light, and shadow, Supernal Memories carries an underlying message of optimism through its harmony of seeming dualities – hard and soft, familiar and surprising, expression and introspection.

Each newly generated circle brings its own energy, creating layered groups of light that sometimes resemble phenomena like nebula, lightning sprites, and auras – ethereal whispers of something remembered. 

Supernal Memories is an invitation to observe the forms & feel of each piece without labeling their qualities, to contemplate the infinite possibilities of the universe, and to explore the depths of your imagination.


--

Created by Diego Pintos @DondiegoTez
Creative collaboration with Tender @tender_art

To get a high resolution file, add "&print=14000" to the end of the live URL / hash, using any resolution number that fits your needs. Press 's' to save the file when it is done loading.

Press 'p' to continue the animation for another variation.

100% code, made with p5.js
See license.md

metadata.name: Corroding Cubes #12
metadata.description:
The kaleidoscopic pillars, once soaring emblems of the city's soul, had now succumbed to the relentless onslaught of time. Yet, as they crumbled and decayed, their colors remained steadfast, a radiant symphony of hues that defied the erosion of age. The people looked up at the pillars, and in their decline, they saw a reflection of their own trials and victories.

• • •

All of the visuals in this project are 100% code.

metadata.name: BLOCK PARTY #117
metadata.description:
A generative algorithm exploring isometric grids and recursive divisions with an emphasis on contrasting colors.

A random rectange division is so simple yet creates vastly different and interesting outputs.

An isometric grid provides a unique perspective to the recursion giving each piece a certain depth and contrast.

When does chaotic randomness become beauty and what interesting patterns may emerge?

Press 's' in live mode to save image. Best viewed after save.

* Original code by Matt Lehoullier with p5.js

metadata.name: FX(T)RASH #420
metadata.description:
Imagine having Van Gogh's ear in a little box, getting your grubby hands on Banksy's stencils or Zancan's plotter! Well, here's something just as awesome - This is your chance to collect some trash straight from the King of Trash Art himself, Robness!

---

NOR44 & ROBNESS V2 JOIN FORCES TO CREATE A SPECIAL GENERATIVE PROJECT IN HONOR OF THE SECOND #TEZTRASH EVENT ON 12/21/22.  TEZTRASH IS A TEZOS COMMUNITY DAY WHEN THE CRYPTONATIVE ART MOVEMENT #TRASHART AND TRASH ART IN GENERAL IS CELEBRATED.  THE PREVIOUS TEZTRASH EVENT WAS A MONUMENTAL HIT ON TWITTER AND THIS TIME AROUND WE'VE DECIDED TO CONCOCT AN EPIC GENERATIVE DROP WHILST KEEPING THE TRASH ART ETHOS EMBEDDED IN THE WORK. HERE WE PLAY WITH THE NOTION OF 'TRASHING JPEGS' AND REINSERTING A PHYSICAL YET GENERATIVE REPRESENTATION OF THAT IDEA. ENJOY AND HAPPY TEZTRASH 2.0 DAY!

---

This generative artwork is composed of many layers of pre-rendered images with code utilized to stylize as well as randomly position, rotate and scale these elements, creating potentially infinite unique compositions resembling real-world outputs from a Photocopier/Copy Machine that's seen better days.

metadata.name: (recombination/perspectives)-I: Horizons #64
metadata.description:
🌊 🌞 🌈 🌅


    ( r e c o m b i n a t i o n  /  p e r s p e c t i v e s ) 


                     I :   H o r i z o n s


                            ✨ 🧬 🧡 ⏲







-----
* What/How *

2 560 000 particles are subjected to a succession of 64 energy bursts which scatters the points through space. 
The algorithm then stores 3 configurations of points, forming an entangled coherent system.
After few seconds multiple observation modalities are then selected sequentially to allow for dynamic and contemplative visualization.

-----
* Mint preview *

Minter will get a 2160x2160 PNG bitmap and an infinite randomly deterministic animation.

-----
* Technics *

This experience is designed to be executed on a recent GPU (>2016) and displayed on 16/9 screens from FHD to 8K+ (1920x1080 → 7680x4320) at 60FPS for infinite duration.

- JavaScript / ThreeJS / WebGL / GLSL
- Unique generative, random and determinist animation (animation is seeded by the fxhash mint hash)
- Infinite animation
- Animation sequences duration between 6 and 60 seconds.

-----
* Controls *

Keyboard "Space" : take a PNG capture of the current view frame (same ratio as window, max 1920x1080)

Keyboard "X" : skip current animation sequence / next sequence

-----
* URL modifiers *

"&fastdemo=on"
Forces animation sequences to last 10 seconds instead of random durations.

"&slow=on"
Forces animation sequences to last 1 minute instead of random durations.

"&static=on"
Disables animation automatic start. Press "X" to start animations.


-----
@HAL09999 – January 25th, 2023

metadata.name: Flume #133
metadata.description:
Flume are infinitely flowing digital bodies of water.
The flow of Flumes can range from slow and gentle, creating small ripples and eddies, to fast and turbulent, carving its way through the inner workings of your computer screen. 
The color, clarity, and viscosity of the water can also vary.

This is the culmination of my collection Flume, an exploration into On-Chain art on Ethereum, https://etherscan.io/address/0x1fa23513825f952afca07a603ac3f312ebee4ca9

These pieces were all created in p5js.

- Andrew

metadata.name: Atom Heart Mother #9
metadata.description:
This artwork is an attempt to create a calming landscape view of a valley leading up to the hills.

It's coded entirely in p5.js and is best viewed on a screen bigger than a mobile phone, while listening to this track called ‘Atom Heart Mother' by Pink Floyd: https://open.spotify.com/album/2cUpAOlQjV5uSjkWj5bEQY

Artwork loads at 1000px by 1000px resolution by default. Press ‘2’,’4’ or ‘8’ to load as 2000px by 2000px, 4000px by 4000px or 8000px by 8000px respectively. Press 's' at any time to download the rendered resolution.

metadata.name: Dithered Nostalgia #163
metadata.description:
Have you ever struck by a sudden surge of nostalgia?
Making you stop everything you did at that moment,
Trying hard to remember the memory behind it, and failed to do so?

Each of these lands hold a nostalgia unlocked,
Like how good nostalgia are, it’s dithered and full of holes.
Holes that can be filled with your own memories and interpretations.

• • •

The second collaboration of MEK.txt and IceRain in FXHash. This time using MEK.txt’s landscape pixelart series and its distinctive dithering textures, brilliantly translated into code by IceRain to pixel-perfect iterations.

Dithered Nostalgia is a step up from MEK.txt & IceRain’s first project (Bento Boxes), trying to make more sophisticated, more detailed and challenging things based on something they passionate about; landscape.

Controls:
[1] Set the resolution to Medium Resolution
[2] Set the resolution to High Resolution

metadata.name: Awaiting Yesterday (SoC: Apr) #45
metadata.description:
Awaiting Yesterday On A Foggy Morning (SoC: Apr)

This is the memory of my childhood hometown,
mountains, trees, high sky and wet air, 
all of them are mixed in a silence and foggy morning, 
only birds fly out of woods.

--------------------------

This is also the third work of a larger portfolio of work 'State of Coherence' (SoC) which explores and describes the coherence of people, cultures and the objective world.

--------------------------

This is a generation artwork made by pure code.
In live mode, press 's' or 'S' to save a high resolution png.

Please be patient with drawing process (it'll take about 15s in my computer).
Enjoy~

Endlessworld
April, 2023
